'''''Star Wars Insider'' 85''' is the 85th issue of [[Star Wars Insider]], released [[November]] [[2005]].

It started shipping to subscribers the week of [[November 14]], and shipped to newsstands the week of [[November 28]].<ref name="Dates">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20051101.html|text=More Vader in ''Star Wars Insider'' #85}}</ref>

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]: News from Around the Galaxy"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide|From Droids to Darths]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic (comic series)|For Over a Thousand Generations...]] {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; ''Invisible Hand'': Main Bridge {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; Starting With A Clean Slate {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; How To Insure Your Collection... And Still Eat! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars Unleashed|Unleash Your Inner Collector]] {{C|by Brett Rector}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; The Iron Chef Of Filmmaking {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 16 {{C|edited by [[Mary Franklin]]}}

===Features===
*"[[The Saga is Now Complete]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>The #1 movie of the year is now out! ''Insider'' descended upon the serene confines of Skywalker Ranch to get all the details on the ''Revenge of the Sith'' DVD as well as get the scoop on the exciting new LucasArts game, Battlefront II!</small>
*"[[The Art of Revenge of the Sith]], Part Three" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>''Insider'' concludes its series with a great collection of artistic gems that you positively won't see or read about anywhere else.</small>
*"[[A Two-Edged Sword]]" {{C|by [[Karen Traviss]]}}
*:<small>Darth Vader is one tough customer, but even he needs help to dispatch six fearsome Dark Jedi clones.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in the Delegation of 2000]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Now that the ''Revenge of the Sith'' DVD is out, fans get to see deleted scenes that show the "birth" of the Rebellion. ''Insider'' reveals the details on a brave bunch of Senators who dared to try and defy the Chancellor.</small>
*"[[Long Ago, Far Away: Galaxy Fashion]]" {{C|by [[Cherie Buchheim]]}}
*:<small>In celebration of the "Dressing a Galaxy" exhibit at the FIDM museum in Los Angeles, California, ''Insider'' made a visit to check out Trisha Biggar's work firsthand. What we saw can only be described as phenomenal.</small>
*"[[Posters of Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back|Posters of Episode V: ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]" {{C|by [[Pete Vilmur]]}}
*:<small>In part two of a three-part series, poster collector Pete Vilmur provides a once-in-a-lifetime look at rare concepts from the 1980 movie. And hey, just in time to celebrate its 25th birthday!</small>

